Diagnosis. Yellow species; anterior cercus of the male terminalia with proclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
Figs 102, 103
) and with descendant plate subrectangular in posterior view (
Fig. 105
); phallus subcylindrical with dorsal, subapical, narrow appendix, best visualized in lateral view (
Fig. 107
), and spiniform projections, more conspicuous in ventral view (
Fig. 108
); genital fork with arms fused at apex (
Fig. 112
); tergite 10 undivided (
Fig. 111
).

